    management: ["Implement prescribing agreements with clear expectations for duration, dose limits, and monitoring","Never co-prescribe benzodiazepines with opioids unless alternatives exhausted and benefits outweigh risks","Use lowest effective dose for shortest duration; reassess need at every visit","Develop tapering protocol for discontinuation: 10-25% reduction every 1-2 weeks","Switch to longer-acting agent (diazepam) for taper from short-acting benzodiazepines to prevent interdose withdrawal","Consider alternative anxiolytics: buspirone (non-sedating, no dependence), hydroxyzine, gabapentin for anxiety management"],
    nursingActions: ["Monitor for signs of benzodiazepine misuse: dose escalation, multiple prescribers, lost prescriptions, combination with alcohol","Educate patients about dependence risk: physical dependence can develop within 2-4 weeks of daily use","Counsel on avoidance of alcohol, opioids, and other CNS depressants during benzodiazepine therapy","Assess for withdrawal symptoms during taper: anxiety rebound, insomnia, tremor, diaphoresis, seizure risk","Monitor falls risk in elderly: implement fall prevention protocols and environmental safety measures","Document and report any concerning patterns: early refill requests, altered prescriptions, medication diversion"],
